RESEARCH_MUNICIPALITY.notes: Lynnwood, WA operates under a mayor-council government. George Hurst is the Mayor-elect, having led in the November 2025 elections against incumbent Christine Frizzell. The City Council consists of seven members elected at-large. Recent election results from November 2025 indicate Derica Escamilla and Robert Leutwyler retained their seats, Isabel Mata was elected to Position 2, and Bryce Owings was elected to Position 3. Rebecca Thornton was appointed as a Council Member in February 2025. Nick Coelho and David Parshall are also current council members.
